. The other one is not so much concerned with the relation of dream and meaning, of dream and reality, it rather concentrates on trying to find means of representation for this extremely productive force that determines our sleep. The essays collected in this book explore both attempts. They follow debates in philosophy and psychoanalysis and they study literature, theatre, dance, film, and photography.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 16. Mai 2019) 0aDreams in art. 0aDreams in literature. 0aDreams in motion pictures. 0aDreams. 4aDream. 4aFilm. 4aLiteratur. 4aTanz. 4aTheater. 4aTraumdarstellung. 4adance. 4aunconsciousness. 4avisual arts. 70(DE-601)1044348800(DE-588)4045895-7aFotografie2gnd 70(DE-601)1057089680(DE-588)4129566-3aDarstellende Kunst2gnd 70(DE-601)1058007400(DE-588)4117245-0aTraumgMotiv2gnd 70(DE-601)1061385450(DE-588)4060747-1aTraum2gnd 70(DE-601)1061938800(DE-588)4047689-3aPsychoanalyse2gnd 70(DE-601)1062002590(DE-588)4045791-6aPhilosophie2gnd 70(DE-601)1062450150(DE-588)4035964-5aLiteratur2gnd 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aHahn, Barbara, eeditor.1 aWerner, Meike, eeditor.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2016z9783110485264oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97831104335310 cprintz978311043751540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110433852423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110433852.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  